The paper focuses on using computer graphics and Generative Adversarial Networks to generate and augment labeled data for training deep neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the performance of the trained model, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of computer graphics and image synthesis also suggests a potential fit for graphics (cs.GR) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
